column169: On April 2, 2024, one (1) 55-gallon drum of resin solution was punctured by the shipper's skid and released approximately two (2) gallons of product to the trailer interior. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from Thin Line Environmental (TLE) to remediate the impacted site. TLE personnel utilized hand tools, cleaners, absorbents, and a sprayer unit to remediate the site. All spent absorbents and debris were collected and containerized into two (2) 35-gallon drums. The damaged 55-gallon drum of product was placed into one (1) 85-gallon drum. All containers were staged onsite for future disposal.

column169: On April 1, 2024, one (1) 55-gallon drum of UN3901 was damaged in transit due to unknown causes and released approximately 55-gallons of product to the trailer floor, pallets, and concrete. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from EnvioServe (ES) to remediate the impacted site. Crews deployed additional granular absorbents to the impacted area and worked them in with hand tools. Cleaners and absorbent pads were utilized to remove any residual product. The impacted pallet was dismantled for disposal. The dismantled pallet, the damaged drum, all UN3901 impacted materials, and spent absorbents were collected and containerized into one (1) 85-gallon overpack drum and nine (9) 55-gallon drums for disposal by R+L.

Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 30 -gallons of product released to the entire trailer floor and a 15’ x 10’ area of the asphalt and concrete lot below due to a forklift puncture. column169: XPO Logistics terminal UPH experienced an over the road release of UN1866 Tremco Puma Primer from a 6-gallon metal pail. ERTS dispatched contractors to conduct containment and cleanup. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 2-gallons of product released due to a broken pallet puncturing the pail. The majority of the release impacted a 6’ x 4’ area of the wooden trailer floor with approximately 1 cup impacting a 3” x 6” area of the gravel rocks below the trailer. The damaged pail was collected with oil dri into a 55-gallon metal drum. Absorbent pads were then used to clean the impacted trailer and crew utilized hand tools to scrap up the impacted rocks. The impacted rags, damaged pallet, impacted gravel rocks, PPE, and poly were placed into a separate 55-gallon metal drum. The waste was transported back to the XPO terminal in Phoenix, AZ for terminal personnel to manage.

XPO-XNJ contacted ERTS regarding (6) damaged 1-gallon jugs of Heavy Duty Foam Degreaser that fell  during transit as a result of improper loading / improper blocking and bracing. Approximately 2-gallons of product released onto the concrete dock floor. A Contractor overpacked the damaged product and neutralized  the impacted boxes, plastic, cardboard, and trash can liners using Citri Acid. Three drums of waste were  generated for disposal. No storm-drains, waterways, or soil were affected by this incident.
